<item>
            <title>[JDK-8302111] Serialization considerations</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8302111</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>While addressing JDK-8286503, it was noted that there may be other S11N issues which are more of a functional/data consistency nature.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Essentially, deserialization is a form of object construction and should enforce the same data validation and consistency checks as enforced by the constructor(s). Thus, additional checks may be needed when deserializing the objects to ensure that values failing the constructor check are rejected during deserialization as well.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
